</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>ACR182:v96#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="ACR182"/><meta name="dc:title" content="ACR &#xA;              182-&#xA;                CHAPTERED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div width="100%" style="text-align:center;"><div id="bill_num_title_chap"><span style="text-align:center;font-weight:bold;font-size:1.1em;font-family:'Times New Roman'; "><b>
                Assembly Concurrent Resolution
              
                        No. 182</b></span></div><div style="text-align:center;padding-top: 1.0em;padding-bottom: 1.2em;" id="chap_num_title_chap"><span style="font-size:1.4em;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;">
                      CHAPTER 116</span></div></div><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;">Relative to Youth Mental Health Awareness Week in California.</span></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center">
                  
                  [<span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Filed with
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Secretary of State
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">June 18, 2026.
                      </span>]
                </div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">ACR 182, Ransom.
                          Youth Mental Health Awareness Week in California.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would designate May 3, 2026, to May 9, 2026, inclusive, as Youth Mental Health Awareness Week in California.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_9D68A214-82EF-4F91-9A45-27B416E9C841"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Mental health must be prioritized with the same urgency as physical health; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_651D69D1-3ABD-4379-9C70-EA2BF1BDB257"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, It is important for our youth to thrive and have a positive quality of life, which cannot be achieved without taking care of their mental health; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_4DD8CDE4-8BF8-44EA-8B46-735AB4741862"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Mental health plays a significant role in the overall well-being of youth, thus the importance to recognize and support mental health services for them; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_CFB6C1C6-0AED-41FA-882F-7D4C25F3C8A8"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, It is important to foster inclusivity for our youth, who, with the rise of social media influence, have been subject to negative psychological effects; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_0E7A3808-308F-480E-A942-8C2A9E006128"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Mental health plays a pivotal role in the everyday lives of youth. It is between 12 and 25 years of age when we learn to navigate the world; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_8BA48160-5DF9-448F-9EBD-9F5A7B5A06A5"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Mental health can significantly influence how children and youth behave in their daily lives; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_57BACEA4-034B-4DDD-90DC-A6A7ED00D3D5"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Schools have the ability to foster inclusive, safe, supportive, respectful, and empowering environments for students who are suffering from mental illnesses; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_90EDF5BA-BEB0-4E4A-9888-69F4F2B084D4"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Young people are rapidly learning social and emotional skills that shape their future ability to learn and adapt into different situations of life; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_CFCD2223-C9D3-419F-84DD-00A247AA792B"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Youth mental health programs should address trauma, while promoting resilience, healing, and the pursuit of academic success for all students; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_E4843024-7206-4E03-A3F4-E1011DFEBFCB"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Prioritizing mental health in our youth and providing them with resources can help reduce stigma and cultivate a culture of resilience, support, and compassion within schools and communities; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_D03E4ADF-BB3D-413B-B624-94011D0A775E"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, It is essential to designate a week dedicated to recognizing the mental health of our youth and supporting their well-being; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_80C2C717-E0F2-4CB6-8016-73267D8350EE"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly of the State of California, the Senate thereof concurring, That the Legislature hereby designates May 3, 2026, to May 9, 2026, inclusive, as Youth Mental Health Awareness Week in California; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_8385AECB-E489-4D5F-B37B-8D9E880A350A"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
